/target
/dist
target-local/
# voices_live/<name>/ plugins each carry their own target/ when
# `live_reload::build_and_load` invokes cargo with --target-dir
# crate_root/target. Keep those out of the repo too.
voices_live/*/target/
voices_live/target/

# CARGO_TARGET_DIR may point elsewhere; keep the default rule too.
# /dist is trunk's default output for the web demo.

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace

# Local state from oh-my-claudecode plugin
.omc/

# Per-PR brief from the dispatch chain — the spawning issue (e.g. #44
# for the multi-family roadmap) carries the canonical task brief; the
# working-tree copy of the latest brief is just the dispatcher's
# hand-off envelope and shouldn't bloat the repo. Existing
# already-committed `.dispatch/` design notes (cp-design / soundboard /
# voice-unify) stay tracked.
.dispatch/guitar-brief.md
.dispatch/guitar-corpus-brief.md

# Logs / scratch
*.log
*.tmp

# bench artifacts + acquired audio data
# NEVER commit acquired sound data, sample libraries, or impulse responses.
# Many free-licence packs are CC-BY / CC-NC and DO NOT permit redistribution
# in a derived repo. Even CC0 packs add MB-GB of binary noise to git history.
# This includes reference/*.wav (Iowa MIS, MAPS, etc.) -- documented in
# reference/README.md but never redistributed in this repo.
bench-out/*
!bench-out/REF/
!bench-out/REF/**
# GUI visual-verify screenshots referenced from PR descriptions.
# Small (~200 KB), one-off, useful for review without separate image
# hosting. Renders themselves stay gitignored.
!bench-out/gui-verify/
!bench-out/gui-verify/*.png
# bench-out/songs/ — public-domain MIDI catalog for guitar/piano voice
# testing. Only .mid + manifest.json + README.md are committed; rendered
# WAVs land under bench-out/songs/<engine>/ at user request and stay
# gitignored (the global **/*.wav rule below catches them).
!bench-out/songs/
!bench-out/songs/*.mid
!bench-out/songs/manifest.json
!bench-out/songs/README.md
recordings/
samples/
ir/
reference/*.wav
**/*.wav
# Permissive guitar corpus: a single deterministic fixture WAV is
# committed as the offline-test smoke target. All other WAVs under
# bench-out/REF/guitar/{single_note,chord,corpus}/ are fetched on
# demand by `bench-out/REF/guitar/fetch.sh`.
!bench-out/REF/guitar/single_note/E2_open.wav
# Whitelist the locked-in deterministic reference WAV (square C4) and its
# README, even though the global **/*.wav rule above would otherwise hide
# them. This is the only audio file we redistribute in the repo.
!bench-out/REF/square_c4_4s.wav
!bench-out/REF/sfz_salamander_grand_v3_C4.wav
!bench-out/REF/README.md
!bench-out/REF/sfz_salamander_multi/
!bench-out/REF/sfz_salamander_multi/**
# Guitar reference samples (issue #44 — first non-piano voice family).
# Downloaded on demand by `tools/fetch-guitar-refs.sh` from the
# CC0-licensed Discord SFZ GM Bank. Repo carries the LICENSE.txt and
# README.md so provenance travels even when the WAVs are absent;
# the WAVs themselves stay un-committed per the multi-family brief.
!bench-out/REF/guitar/
!bench-out/REF/guitar/LICENSE.txt
!bench-out/REF/guitar/README.md
# CP E2E demo log: tests/cp_e2e_demo.sh writes the captured PR evidence
# here. Whitelist the directory so run.log is checkable, but keep the
# rendered WAVs and keysynth's verbose stderr tail local-only.
!bench-out/cp-e2e/
!bench-out/cp-e2e/run.log
bench-out/cp-e2e/*.wav
bench-out/cp-e2e/*.stderr.log
bench-out/cp-e2e/*-body.md
# Voice-unify E2E demo log: tests/voice_unify_e2e.sh writes the
# captured PR evidence here. Same policy as cp-e2e: whitelist the log,
# keep WAVs / latency tsv / stderr local-only.
!bench-out/voice-unify/
!bench-out/voice-unify/run.log
bench-out/voice-unify/*.wav
bench-out/voice-unify/keysynth.stderr.log
bench-out/voice-unify/reload_latency.tsv
**/*.flac
**/*.aif
**/*.aiff
**/*.mp3
**/*.mp4
**/*.webm
**/*.mkv
**/*.ogg
**/*.opus
**/*.m4a
**/*.aac
**/*.wma
# Standard MIDI files acquired from third-party sites (bitmidi, archive.org,
# Mutopia, piano-midi.de, etc.) often have ambiguous redistribution terms even
# when the underlying score is public domain. Keep the whole bench-out/MIDI/
# tree local-only. Hand-authored .mid produced by our own tooling can be
# explicitly whitelisted under bench-out/REF/ when needed.
**/*.mid
**/*.midi
!bench-out/REF/**/*.mid
!bench-out/REF/**/*.midi
# Public-domain song catalog (Mutopia, Traditional). Verified provenance
# in bench-out/songs/manifest.json. Only the curated set is committable;
# kssong-generated chord-progression demos and other ephemeral renders
# stay local-only via the deny rules below.
!bench-out/songs/*.mid
bench-out/songs/bright_*.mid
bench-out/songs/modern_*.mid
bench-out/songs/rhythm_*.mid
bench-out/songs/duet_*.mid
# JSON transcriptions emitted by listener-lab from copyrighted audio are
# derivative works — keep them out of git the same as the source mp3s.
bench-out/CHIPTUNE/
**/*.sf2
**/*.sf3
**/*.sfz
# Exception: the web demo build bundles a small GM SoundFont so Pages
# can run the sf-piano engine without a separate fetch step. ~32 MB.
!web/GeneralUser-GS.sf2
**/*.dls
# Compressed bundles users may drop in (sample packs, IR libraries)
*.zip
*.rar
*.7z
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.tar.bz2
*.tbz2

# SFZ sample libraries (Salamander Grand V3, etc.). The .sfz manifests are
# small text, but the linked WAVs are GB-scale; gitignore the whole tree
# including any uncompressed Salamander dump the user drops in.
Salamander/
sfz-libraries/
.claude/worktrees/
